title: Want To Buy:  Attention all ammo sellers/buyers
postcontent: Did I miss something here? Is it national crack smoking week in the gun community? Why do I keep seeing overpriced ammo posts on this website? I don't know if you people realize, but ammo in just about any caliber is widely available at the moment, most of it at affordable prices. Dicks, walmart, and most of the local gunshops have ammo in stock at prices that aren't necessarily ideal, but affordable. There are also hundreds of companies selling ammo online. Gunbot.net and ammoseek.com are both excellent websites for seeking out the best deals. We need to stop feeding these leeches that seek nothing but to exploit and profit  from decent members of the gun community. When you see people selling overpriced ammo, dont buy it, mark it as overpriced and seek out better deals. Be a proactive buyer, create a demand for low priced ammo and it'll slowly make it's way back.

postcontent:
I have a Remington 870 Police Magnum that doesn't see much use I would like to sell. It has factory tritium night sights and the stock has been upgraded to a magpul and a Scattergun Technologies (Wilson Combat) +2 extension was added. It will come with the original box and paperwork as well as the box and extra spacers for the Magpul stock.

I'm sure I will get a lot of questions of why this costs more than a basic 870 you see in a typical sporting goods store. Those are standard "express" actions even on the tactical models. They have a plastic trigger guard assembly, a weak MIM (metal injection molded) extractor, a week ejector, and most often just a plain bead sight. They also aren't made to nearly the quality the "Police" actions are and also have a cheap teflon finish. 

The Police actions use a metal trigger guard assembly, a heavy duty ejector, a milled extractor, and have a very nice parkerized finish. They are held to a much higher quality standard and the parts like the mag tube, and sights and hit temperature soldered. This model features adjustable tritium night sights (both front and rear). This is a buy once, cry once purchase that will last generations.

I have well over $800 into this shotgun and thats was getting a very good deal on it from Trader Jerry's. Most local shops sell this shotgun in the $750 range in factory form. I will take $600 for it FIRM. I will not take any less and I'm not interested in any trades.
